&#13;
			<div id="ftn208">&#13;
				<p><b><b><i><i><a href="#_ftnref208" name="_ftn208" id="_ftn208"><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span>[208]</span></span></span></span></a> In Pahang, the Syariah Criminal Enactment 2013 does not punish sexual relations between women. However, sexual relations between women are criminalized under an older law, the Administration of the Religion of Islam and the Malay Custom of Pahang Enactment 1982 (Section 150); http://www2.esyariah.gov.my/esyariah/mal/portalv1/enakmen2011/Eng_enactment_Ori_lib.nsf/100ae747c72508e748256faa00188094/f6d243cd5569765e482576b30027f88a?OpenDocument (accessed August 8, 2014). </i></i></b></b></p>&#13;
			</div>&#13;
&#13;
			<div id="ftn209">&#13;
				<p><b><b><i><i><a href="#_ftnref209" name="_ftn209" id="_ftn209"><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span><span class="MsoFootnoteReference"><span>[209]</span></span></span></span></a> JAKIM, E-Fatwa Portal, http://www.e-fatwa.gov.my/fatwa-kebangsaan/pertukaran-jantina-daripada-lelaki-kepada-perempuan (accessed July 21, 2014). This is the official JAKIM translation.</i></i></b></b></p>&#13;
			</div>&#13;
		</div>&#13;
	</div>&#13;
</div>&#13;

    </div>
  </div>

  </div>
</div>

  </div>

              </div>
            </div>
        
            
    </div>
  



